    <bioghist>
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Middlesex County was named probably for the English county. It was formed from Lancaster County by 30 October 1669. The county seat is Saluda. 
</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Middlesex County (Va.) Free Negro and Slave Records, 1764-1802 include free negro affidavits and certificates, bills of sale and receipts related to sell of slaves, and a document recording the emancipation of a slave named Sam.
</p>
          </scopecontent>
